Toss beef with soy sauce; set aside. In large skillet over medium heat, saute rice-vermicelli mix, margarine and onion until vermicelli is golden brown, stirring frequently. Slowly stir in water and seasonings; bring to a boil. Cover; reduce heat to low. Simmer 10 minutes. Stir in beef. Add broccoli and bell pepper; return to a simmer. Cover; simmer 5 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender. Stir before serving.